{"title_page": "Alejandra Guzm\u00e1n", "text_new": "{{short description|Mexican actress and musician}}\n{{Spanish name|Guzm\u00e1n|Pinal}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name         = Alejandra Guzm\u00e1n \n| image        = Alejandra Guzm\u00e1n La Voz 2019.jpg\n| caption      = Guzm\u00e1n performing on [[La Voz (American TV series)|La Voz US]] in 2019\n| birth_name   = Gabriela Alejandra Guzm\u00e1n Pinal\n| birth_date   = {{birth date and age|1968|2|9}}\n| birth_place  = [[Mexico City|Mexico City, Mexico]]\n| alias = {{flatlist|\n* La Reina del Rock\n* La Guzm\u00e1n\n}}\n| occupation   = {{flatlist|\n* Singer-Songwriter\n* Actress\n* Musician\n}}\n| years_active = 1988\u2013present\n| children = 1\n| spouse   = {{marriage|Farell Goodman|1998|1998|reason=divorced}}<br>{{marriage|Gerardo G\u00f3mez|2002|2004|reason=divorce}}\n| website      = {{URL|www.aleguzman.com|www.aleguzman.com\n}}\n| module = {{Infobox musical artist|embed=yes\n| background = solo_singer\n| instrument = {{flatlist|\n* [[Vocals]]\n* [[Guitar]]\n}}\n| genre        = {{flatlist|\n* [[Pop music|Pop]]\n* [[pop rock|Pop Rock]] \n* [[Rock en espa\u00f1ol]]\n}}\n| label       = {{flatlist| \n* [[Sony Music|Sony BMG]]\n* [[Universal Music Group]]\n* [[Independent record label|Independent]]\n}}\n| associated_acts    = {{flatlist|\n* [[Franco De Vita]]\n* [[Gloria Trevi]]\n}}\n}}\n}}\n\n'''Gabriela Alejandra Guzm\u00e1n Pinal''' (born February 9, 1968), known professionally as '''Alejandra Guzm\u00e1n''', is a [[Mexico|Mexican]] singer-songwriter, actress, and musician. She has sold over 30 million albums throughout her career, making her one of the most successful Mexican female singers. She is the daughter of actress [[Silvia Pinal]] and singer [[Enrique Guzm\u00e1n]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.aleguzman.com/?page_id=43|title=Biografia de Alejandra Guzm\u00e1n}}</ref><!---NOTE: Biography from Guzm\u00e1n\u2019s official website, states full name is Gabriela Alejandra Guzm\u00e1n Pinal--->\n\n== Early life and career ==\nGabriela Alejandra Guzm\u00e1n Pinal was born February 9, 1968 in [[Mexico City]], to her mother\u2019s third marriage. Guzm\u00e1n has three siblings: two older half-sisters, actress [[Sylvia Pasquel]] and Viridiana Alatriste. Her younger brother, Luis Enrique Guzm\u00e1n is her only sibling from the same father and mother. \n\nHer first song ''[[Bye Mam\u00e1]]'', a song dedicated to her mom was the start to her career in 1988. In 1990s, she released several of her biggest albums like ''[[Eternamente Bella]]'', ''Flor de Piel'', as well as ''[[Libre (Alejandra Guzm\u00e1n album)|Libre]]'' which launched with a signed contract to [[Sony BMG|BMG Ariola]]. Her success placed her in being nominated to a [[Grammy]], [[Latin Grammy]], and her albums to be labed Gold and Platinum. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://andina.pe/agencia/noticia-esta-cancion-hizo-llorar-a-mama-alejandra-guzman-558889.aspx/go.participate.com/video|title=Esta canci\u00f3n hizo llorar a la mam\u00e1 de Alejandra Guzm\u00e1n|date=June 2, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/eternamente-bella-mw0000644089|title=Eternamente Bella - Alejandra Guzm\u00e1n {{!}} Songs, Reviews, Credits</ref>\n\nWith all her success, she has been labeled to be ''La Reina del Rock'', and one of the most successful female artists of [[Mexico]].\n\nThroughout her career, she has had success throughout [[Mexico]] and the [[United States]]. She has done duets with [[Franco De Vita]], [[Mario Domm]], [[Fonseca (singer)|Fonseca]], and the most known [[Gloria Trevi]]. Her along with Trevi had several duets together and did the [[:es:Versus Tour|Versus Tour]] together from 2017-2018.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin/8317961/alejandra-guzman-gloria-trevi-versus-tour-best-moments|title=Alejandra Guzman & Gloria Trevi on the 'Versus' Tour: Look Back On Their Top 5 Moments|work=Billboard|date= April 14, 2018}}</ref>\n\nShe served as judge of the second season of ''[[Univision|Va Por Ti]]''. She also served as coach of ''[[La Voz (Mexican TV series)|La Voz...M\u00e9xico]]''. On July 5, 2018, [[Telemundo]] announced Alejandra Guzm\u00e1n as a coach on [[La Voz (American TV series)|La Voz (U.S.).]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin/8464061/alejandra-guzman-joins-la-voz-coach-telemundo|title=Alejandra Guzman Joins Telemundo's 'La Voz (The Voice)' as a Coach on the First Season|work=Billboard|access-date=2018-10-22}}</ref> Guzm\u00e1n joins [[Luis Fonsi]], [[Carlos Vives]] and [[Wisin]] as coaches on the Spanish-language version of [[NBC]] singing-competition ''[[The Voice (U.S. TV series)|The Voice]]''.\n\n== Personal life ==\nAlejandra Guzm\u00e1n has had several relationships throughout her life. Her first public relationship was with [[Erik Rubin]] which did not last long due to conflict with Mexican singer [[Paulina Rubio]] over him. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.quien.com/espectaculos/2019/12/03/alejandra-guzman-revive-rivalidad-paulina-rubio-erik-rubin|title=Alejandra Guzm\u00e1n revive su rivalidad con Paulina Rubio por Erik Rub\u00edn|date= December 3, 2019}}</ref> She later, started a relationship with Pablo Moctezuma a businessman whom Guzm\u00e1n has a daughter with, Fr\u00edda Sof\u00eda, born March 1992. Moctezuma and her later separated.\n\nGuzm\u00e1n married to American businessman Farrell Goodman in 1998. The marriage was destroyed right after, when Goodman was arrested due to carrying [[Narcotic|narcotics]] in an airport in [[Germany]]. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.debate.com.mx/show/Quienes-han-sido-las-parejas-de-Alejandra-Guzman-20191129-0095.html|title=Qui\u00e9nes han sido las parejas de Alejandra Guzm\u00e1n|date=November 29, 2019}}</ref> Her last public relationship to date was a little after her divorce with Goodman, with Gerardo G\u00f3mez de la Borbolla. They got married in 2002 and a few months later Guzm\u00e1n announced her second pregnancy. She lost the baby before a little before knowing the [[gender]] of the baby. Guzm\u00e1n was dragged into a deep [[depression (mood)|depression]] due to the loss causing the divorce of her second marriage in 2004.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.canalrcn.com/la-guzman/novedades/estos-fueron-los-principales-amores-de-la-vida-de-alejandra-guzman-16|title=Estos cuerno los principales amores de la vida de Alejandra Guzm\u00e1n}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n===Studio albums===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Release date\n! Title\n|-\n| 1988\n| ''[[Bye Mam\u00e1]]''\n|-\n| 1989\n| ''[[Dame Tu Amor (EP)|Dame Tu Amor]]''\n|-\n| 1990\n| ''[[Eternamente Bella]]''\n|-\n| 1991\n| ''[[Flor de Papel]]''\n|-\n| 1993\n| ''[[Libre (Alejandra Guzm\u00e1n album)|Libre]]''\n|-\n| 1994\n| ''[[Enorme (album)|Enorme]]''\n|-\n| 1996\n| ''[[Cambio de Piel (Alejandra Guzm\u00e1n album)|Cambio de Piel]]''\n|-\n| 1999\n| ''[[Algo Natural (album)|Algo Natural]]''\n|-\n| 2001\n| ''[[Soy (Alejandra Guzm\u00e1n album)|Soy]]''\n|-\n| 2004\n| ''[[Lipstick (Alejandra Guzm\u00e1n album)|Lipstick]]''\n|-\n| 2006\n| ''[[Indeleble]]''\n|-\n| 2007\n| ''[[Fuerza]]''\n|-\n| 2009\n| ''[[\u00danico (Alejandra Guzm\u00e1n album)|\u00danico]]''\n|-\n| 2015\n| ''[[A + No Poder]]''\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''Versus'' {{small|(with [[Gloria Trevi]])}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/mx/album/versus/id1243755076|title=Versus de Gloria Trevi en Apple Music|work=[[iTunes Store]] (MX)|accessdate=11 July 2017}}</ref>\n|}\n\n===Compilation albums===\n* ''[[Reina de Corazones (album)|Reina de Corazones]]''\n* ''[[15 \u00c9xitos (Alejandra Guzm\u00e1n album)|15 \u00c9xitos]]''\n* ''[[Fuerza]]'' (Spanish edition)\n\n===Live albums===\n* ''[[La Guzm\u00e1n]]''\n* ''[[Alejandra Guzman En Vivo]]''\n* ''[[20 A\u00f1os de \u00c9xitos En Vivo con Moderatto]]''\n* ''[[La Guzm\u00e1n: Primera Fila]]''\n* ''La Guzm\u00e1n Live at the Roxy\n\n===Singles===\n[[File:Alejandra_Guzm\u00e1n_at_Denver_Coliseum.jpg|thumb|right|250px|Alejandra Guzm\u00e1n at Denver Coliseum, 2009.]]\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! align=\"center\" rowspan=\"2\" | Year\n! align=\"center\" rowspan=\"2\" | Single\n! align=\"center\" colspan=\"2\" | Chart positions<ref>[{{BillboardURLbyName|artist=alejandra guzm\u00e1n|chart=all}} \"Alejandra Guzman: Billboard Singles\"]</ref>\n|-\n! width=\"60\" | <small>'''U.S. Hot Latin Songs'''</small>\n! width=\"60\" | <small>'''U.S. Latin Pop Airplay'''</small>\n|-\n| align=\"center\" rowspan=\"1\" | 1990\n| align=\"left\" | \"Eternamente Bella\"\n| align=\"center\" | 20\n| align=\"center\" | -\n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\" align=\"center\" | 1991\n| align=\"left\" | \"Cuidado con el Coraz\u00f3n\"\n| align=\"center\" | 18\n| align=\"center\" | -\n|-\n| align=\"left\" | \"Rosas Rojas\"\n| align=\"center\" | 36\n| align=\"center\" | -\n|-\n| align=\"left\" | \"[[Reina de Corazones (album)|Reina de Corazones]]\"\n| align=\"center\" | 27\n| align=\"center\" | -\n|-\n| align=\"left\" | \"Hacer el Amor con Otro\"\n| align=\"center\" | 16\n| align=\"center\" | -\n|-\n|align=\"left\" | \"Hey G\u00fcera\"\n|align=\"center\" | -\n|align=\"center\" | -\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" align=\"center\" | 1993\n| align=\"left\" | \"Mala Hierba\"\n| align=\"center\" | 10\n| align=\"center\" | -\n|-\n|\"M\u00edrala, M\u00edralo\"\n|\n|\n|-\n| align=\"center\" rowspan=\"2\" | 1995\n| align=\"left\" | \"Despertar\"<ref>[http://www.billboard.com/charts/1995-04-22/latin-pop-songs \"Despertar: Billboard Latin Pop Airplay\"]</ref>\n| align=\"center\" | 23\n| align=\"center\" | 7\n|-\n| align=\"left\" | \"Morir de Amor\"<ref>[http://www.billboard.com/charts/1995-12-23/latin-pop-songs \"Morir de Amor: Billboard Latin Pop Airplay\"]</ref>\n| align=\"center\" | -\n| align=\"center\" | 14\n|-\n| align=\"center\" rowspan=\"1\" | 2001\n| align=\"left\" | \"[[De Verdad]]\"<ref>[http://www.billboard.com/charts/2002-04-13/latin-pop-songs \"De Verdad: Billboard Latin Pop Airplay\"]</ref>\n| align=\"center\" | 22\n| align=\"center\" | 10\n|-\n| align=\